# Vercel AI SDK — OpenAI Integration

This project uses the [Vercel AI SDK](https://sdk.vercel.ai/) (`ai` + `@ai-sdk/openai`) for all AI features. Never call OpenAI APIs directly.

## Structured Output — Generating Flashcards

Use `generateText` with `Output.object` and a Zod schema to produce structured data. The model is `gpt-4.1-nano` — the cheapest OpenAI model that supports structured outputs ($0.10/1M input, $0.40/1M output).

```typescript
import { generateText, Output } from "ai";
import { openai } from "@ai-sdk/openai";
import { z } from "zod";

const cardSchema = z.object({
  cards: z.array(
    z.object({
      front: z.string(),
      back: z.string(),
    }),
  ),
});

const { output } = await generateText({
  model: openai("gpt-4.1-nano"),
  output: Output.object({ schema: cardSchema }),
  prompt: `Generate ${count} flashcards about ${topic}.`,
});
```

## Rules

- Always use `generateText` from `ai` and `openai` from `@ai-sdk/openai` — never call the OpenAI REST API directly
- Always use `Output.object` with a Zod schema for structured responses — never parse raw text
- Model: `gpt-4.1-nano` via `openai("gpt-4.1-nano")` — cheapest option with structured output support
- AI calls must happen in Server Actions only — never on the client
- Gate AI features behind Clerk Billing (`has({ feature: "ai_flashcard_generation" })`) before invoking
